Functional Mushroom Market Analysis and Size


The functional mushroom market has been experiencing rapid growth, driven by increasing consumer awareness about the health benefits of functional foods and natural supplements. Functional mushrooms, which include varieties like reishi, lion’s mane, cordyceps, and chaga, are widely recognized for their adaptogenic and medicinal properties. These mushrooms are used in dietary supplements, beverages, cosmetics, and functional foods, making them versatile and in high demand.

The global market size for functional mushrooms was valued at approximately USD 26.7 billion in 2022 and is projected to grow at a CAGR of 8.2% between 2023 and 2030. Factors like the growing popularity of plant-based diets, rising consumer preference for natural and organic ingredients, and increasing investments in research and product development are fueling this growth.

