Market Definition
Functional mushrooms are fungi species that offer health benefits beyond basic nutrition. Unlike conventional mushrooms consumed as vegetables, functional mushrooms are rich in bioactive compounds such as beta-glucans, antioxidants, polysaccharides, and triterpenoids. These compounds provide therapeutic effects, such as boosting immunity, enhancing cognitive function, reducing stress, and improving energy levels.

Functional mushrooms are available in various forms, including powders, extracts, capsules, and ready-to-consume products like beverages and snacks. Their applications span across industries such as nutraceuticals, pharmaceuticals, food and beverage, and cosmetics.

